* â€œCruise delay costs accumulate at **$3â€“8k/hour in fuel** before port/slot penalties, overtime, or compensation; cutting **loiter and search time** has immediate OPEX benefit.â€ ([Cruise Hive][2])
* â€œCrisis-communication scholarship shows cruise incidents **damage reputation and demand**; visibly deploying modern MOB tech and producing **audit-grade evidence** mitigates PR exposure.â€ ([IU Indianapolis ScholarWorks][3])
* â€œProbability-weighted UAV search (near-datum plume first) and **rapid buoy/dye/strobe drops** convert a potential **prolonged SAR** into a **controlled recovery narrative**, improving **POS** and **reducing cost/PR risk**.â€ ([IU Indianapolis ScholarWorks][3])

